ation Museum], located in Petersburg, Kentucky\n* [http://humanorigins.si.edu/evidence/human-evolution-timeline-interactive Human Timeline (Interactive)] \u2013 [[Smithsonian Institution|Smithsonian]], [[National Museum of Natural History]] (August 2016).\n{{Creation Science|state=expanded}}\n{{Pseudoscience}}\n{{Creationism topics}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Evolutionary biology|Science}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Creation Science}}\n[[Category:Creation science| ]]\n[[Category:Pseudoscience]]\n", "name_user": "MonicaRLeslie", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eViews on science:Added references for the two following sentences: \"Scientists also deem creation science's attacks against biological evolution to be without scientific merit\" and \"The views of the scientific community were accepted in two significant court decisions in the 1980s, which found the field of creation science to be a religious mode of inquiry, not a scientific one\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Creation_science"}
