{"title_page": "1998 United States Senate election in Louisiana", "text_new": "{{Unreferenced|date=June 2019|bot=noref (GreenC bot)}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name = 1998 United States Senate election in Louisiana\n| country = Louisiana\n| flag_year = 1912\n| type = presidential\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 1992 United States Senate election in Louisiana\n| previous_year = 1992\n| next_election = 2004 United States Senate election in Louisiana\n| next_year = 2004\n| election_date = November 3, 1998\n| image1 = [[File:John Breaux, official photo portrait, standing (cropped).jpg|x150px]]\n| nominee1 = '''[[John Breaux]]'''\n| party1 = Democratic Party (United States)\n| popular_vote1 = '''620,502'''\n| percentage1 = '''64.0%'''\n| image2 = [[File:No image.svg|x120px]]\n| nominee2 = [[Jim Donelon]]\n| party2 = Republican Party (United States)\n| popular_vote2 = 306,616\n| percentage2 = 31.6%\n| map_image = Louisiana Senatorial Election Results by County, 1998.svg\n| map_size = 300px\n| map_caption = Parish Results<br/>'''Breaux:''' {{legend0|#a5b0ff|40\u201350%}} {{legend0|#7996e2|50\u201360%}} {{legend0|#6674de|60\u201370%}} <br>{{legend0|#584cde|70\u201380%}}<br/>'''Donelon:''' {{legend0|#e27f7f|50\u201360%}} \n| title = U.S. Senator\n| before_election = [[John Breaux]]\n| before_party = Democratic Party (United States)\n| after_election = [[John Breaux]]\n| after_party = Democratic Party (United States)\n}}\n{{ElectionsLA}}\nThe '''1998 United States Senate election in Louisiana''' was held November 3, 1998. Incumbent Democratic U.S. Senator [[John Breaux]] won re-election to a third term. As of {{CURRENTYEAR}}, this is the last time the Democrats have won the Class 3 Senate Seat from Louisiana.\n\n== Major candidates ==\n=== Democratic ===\n* [[John Breaux]], incumbent U.S. Senator\n\n=== Republican ===\n* [[Jim Donelon]], State Representative\n\n== Results ==\n{{Election box begin\n | title      = Louisiana United States Senate election, 1998}}\n{